725265f-b.title: Queens: 37th Avenue - Prince Street
725265f-b.text:
(1)
Thirty-seventh Ave. (right), south side, west of Prince Stre
(formerly Garden Street), showing Hamilton Hall at the S.W. corne
This building was erected in 1803 at the corner of Main and Locus
Streets at a cost of ~1250. It then belonged to St. George Episc
Church. The building was eonverted into a sunday school in 1811.
was removed in 1860 to the present site. In 1926 its number was
133-48-50 Thirty-seventh Ave.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
g)he same. an other view.
Eugene L. Armbruster has it that this building was original
St. George's Academy and stood on church property. In 1805 it b
Hamilton Hall, an independent acadeny, then it again reverted to
church.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

725266f-a.title: Queens: 37th Avenue - Prince Street
725266f-a.text:
. 7th AVe., .,at and adjoining the N. W. cerner of Prince St.
In the foreground is a view of the Reformed Church of Flushing.
The congregation was organized in June 1842; the corner stone
laid on August lo, 1843; and the edifice dedicatcd on September
10, 1844. The Rev. A. Gordon was its first pastor. The building
was demolished in 1925. Note: this building was not designated
as a church in the Realty Atlas of Queens for 1891. TThe cost
of the edifice was twelve thousand dollars. It was enlarged in
1859. In 1925 a garage occupied the site of this church. A new
structure was erected in 1892 at the corner of Amity and Bowne
Sts.
Views: 1-3 1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY B. REPRODUCED.

727696f-a.title: Queens: Prince Street - 37th Avenue
727696f-a.text:
Prince Street, at the N.E. corner of 37th Avenue.
The corner house was owned, in 1873, by T. Fogarty, and
the one adjoining it (left) by Mrs. Burling.
P. L. Sperr  June 28, 1940
NO REPRODUCTIONS

727697f-a.title: Queens: Prince Street - 37th Avenue
727697f-a.text:
Prince Street, at the S.E. corner of 37th Avence,
viewing toward the latter and showing old homes. The
corner house was owned, in 1873, by one having the in-
itials P.F.(probably P. Fogarty), according to Beers's
1873 map.
P. L. Sperr  June 28, 1940
NO REPRODUCTIONS

725267f-a.title: Queens: 37th Avenue - Prince Street
725267f-a.text:
Thirty-seventh Ave., south side, east of Prince Street. The
firet fully seen house was occupied by John Hefferman for fifty
years.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
